network

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsutil.generic.state.State
      • network.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Node
extends dsutil.generic.state.State
    A node has the following features: - It extends the state that is a container of information. - It has a number of incoming and outgoing links. - It can be activated/deactivated and connected/disconnected. - It can vary the flow type: the flow can be any information contained in the state Every persistent operation over the list of links imposes a re-evaluation of the node connectivity.
    See Also:
